Package gw.rest.core.pl.framework.v1.refs

Class AbstractKeyableBeanJsonValueResolver<V extends KeyableBean>

java.lang.Object
gw.rest.core.pl.framework.v1.refs.AbstractKeyableBeanJsonValueResolver<V>
Type Parameters:
V - The type of KeyableBean that this resolver resolves to
All Implemented Interfaces:
JsonValueResolver
Direct Known Subclasses:
AttributeJsonValueResolver, GroupJsonValueResolver, KeyableBeanJsonValueResolver, RegionJsonValueResolver, UserJsonValueResolver
public abstract class AbstractKeyableBeanJsonValueResolver<V extends KeyableBean> extends Object implements JsonValueResolver
You may subclass this resolver if you need a KeyableBean JSON value resolver with customizable behavior. If you do not need customizable behavior, the KeyableBeanJsonValueResolver may be sufficient for your needs.

In order for the resolver to work, the schema property must have the x-gw-extensions resourceType set to a resource which is a subtype of DefaultRestElementResource and the path of the updater must resolve to a KeyableBean of type AbstractKeyableBeanJsonValueResolver

By default, resolving by both id and refid is supported. You may turn off resolving by refid by adding "setByRefid": false to the updater.

Optionally, you may also specify 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' and 'rootToAncestorPath'. If 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' is specified, the code will make sure that the resolved value belongs to the same ancestor as the root. For example if 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' is resolvedValue.User and 'rootToAncestorPath' is CustomEntity_Ext.User, then the code will make sure that both the resolved value and root belong to the same User.

Note that the 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' and 'rootToAncestorPath' must both resolve to KeyableBeans that are the same type. 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' must start with the special symbol 'resolvedValue' which will be populated with the AbstractKeyableBeanJsonValueResolver that is found by the resolver code, and 'rootToAncestorPath' must start with the root on the updater.

If you specify 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' but do not specify 'rootToAncestorPath', then the root of the updater will be used as the ancestor to match.
